page.guidelines.commonSense: Use common sense at all times.
page.guidelines.user.profile.0: Your profile must not link to anything objectionable.
page.guidelines.user.profile.1: Your bio must not contain anything objectionable or any links.
page.guidelines.user.profile.2: Custom profile css must not interfere with the website normal functions or be used maliciously.
page.guidelines.user.other.0: You are not permitted to do anything to circumvent any punishment added to your account, doing so will result in another punishment that may be worse or equal to your current one.
page.guidelines.user.other.1: You are not allowed to disclose any malicious bugs or issues to third parties unless it is already available to the general public as a published GitHub security advisory.
page.guidelines.user.other.1.1: If you have found a malicious bug or issue please report it to us via our email listed above.
page.guidelines.bot.listing.0: Your bot must not contain an inappropriate avatar.
page.guidelines.bot.listing.1: Your bot must not contain an inappropriate username.
page.guidelines.bot.listing.2: Your bot's short and long description must be related to your bot.
page.guidelines.bot.listing.3: You may use HTML and Markdown in your bot's long description, if your bot is Verified you will be able to use script tags.
page.guidelines.bot.other.0: Your bot must follow the Discord Terms of Use, Developer Terms of Use and Privacy Policy.
page.guidelines.bot.other.1: Your bot must not respond to other bots or webhooks.
page.guidelines.bot.other.2: Your bot must not go offline for a large period of time and it must be online all the time except for maintenance.
page.guidelines.bot.other.3: Your bot must escape @everyone and @here mentions.
page.guidelines.bot.other.4: Your bot must not automatically send direct messages such as:
page.guidelines.bot.other.4.4: Any other form of messages unless they are invoked by a command.
page.guidelines.bot.other.5: Your bot's primary purpose cannot be as a COVID-19 bot without reviewal from management (You may still submit it but it will go through harsher testing).
page.guidelines.server.listing.0: Your server must not contain an inappropriate avatar.
page.guidelines.server.listing.1: Your server must not contain an inappropriate username.
page.guidelines.server.listing.2: Your server's short and long description must be related to your server.
page.guidelines.server.listing.3: You may use Basic HTML and Markdown in your server's long description, Basic HTML is standard HTML without any styling or scripting abilities.
page.guidelines.server.other.0: Your server must follow the Discord Terms of Service and actively enforce it.
page.guidelines.template.listing.0: Your template must not contain an inappropriate avatar.
page.guidelines.template.listing.1: Your template must not contain an inappropriate username.
page.guidelines.template.listing.2: Your template's short and long description must be related to your template.
page.guidelines.template.listing.3: You may use Basic HTML and Markdown in your template's long description, Basic HTML is standard HTML without any styling or scripting abilities.
page.guidelines.template.other.0: Your template must follow the Discord Terms of Service.
